                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2303: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-22T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 22, 1931—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>243. Drummond has handed me for communication to you the following message from
                    the Japanese delegation dated October 17, which has been circulated to the
                    members of the Council: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The troops from the Shingishu (Korea) garrison which had been sent to
                            Manchuria were all sent back to their garrison on the 16th <pb
                                facs="0409" n="299" xml:id="pg_299"/> instant. I had the honor to
                            inform you in a previous letter that some of these troops were sent back
                            to Korea on September 28th.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
